---
title: Convert to the @nx/detox inferred plugin
description: Migrate off the deprecated @nx/detox:build and @nx/detox:test executors by using the @nx/detox/plugin inferred targets.
sidebar:
  label: Convert to the inferred plugin
filter: 'type:Guides'
---

The `@nx/detox:build` and `@nx/detox:test` executors are deprecated and will be removed in **Nx v24**. The `@nx/detox/plugin` inferred plugin produces equivalent `build`, `test`, and `start` targets directly from your Detox config file, with no executor wrappers. This guide walks through converting existing executor-based targets to the inferred plugin.

Your Detox configuration (`.detoxrc.json` / `detox.config.js`) does not need to change.

## Auto-convert (recommended)

Run the included generator:

```shell
nx g @nx/detox:convert-to-inferred
```

This:

- Removes `@nx/detox:build` and `@nx/detox:test` executor targets from each project
- Ensures `@nx/detox/plugin` is registered in `nx.json` with the right target-name overrides
- Preserves any per-target options (configurations, build target dependencies, etc.) that the inferred plugin can't represent directly

After it runs, the `build`, `test`, and `start` targets on each project come from the inferred plugin.

## Manual setup

If you'd rather wire it yourself, add the plugin to `nx.json`:

```json
// nx.json
{
  "plugins": [
    {
      "plugin": "@nx/detox/plugin",
      "options": {
        "buildTargetName": "build",
        "startTargetName": "start",
        "testTargetName": "test"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Then remove the explicit `build-ios` / `test-ios` / `build-android` / `test-android` targets from each project — the inferred plugin creates them automatically for any project that has a `.detoxrc` file.

The inferred targets shell out to `detox build`, `detox test`, and `detox start` with the project root as `cwd`. They're cached by default and declare `externalDependencies: ['detox']` as an input.

## What stays the same

- `detox` itself remains a peer dependency of `@nx/detox` and continues to work normally.
- The `@nx/detox` package and the `@nx/detox/plugin` inferred plugin remain supported.
- The `@nx/detox:application` generator (invoked when you scaffold an e2e project via `@nx/react-native:application` or `@nx/expo:application` with `e2eTestRunner: 'detox'`) keeps working. New scaffolds emit no executor-based targets when the inferred plugin is registered.
